/* 700 -- charter_terminal: the Constitution's TERMINAL GATE (capability 1).
 *
 * The global run_charter folds all thirteen Harmony-Invariant clauses (H1..H13,
 * h{1..13}_charter.iii / corpus 674,688..699) into one green/red light: GREEN iff every
 * invariant's full self-test passes (verify held, falsifier caught, canary drove RED, sealed
 * verdict reproduced), else the 1-based index of the first failing clause -- which, for the
 * thirteen registered in order, IS the failing invariant's number.  ct_selftest also proves
 * the terminal fold is a REAL falsifier: an injected canary that claims H1 is broken drives
 * the gate RED at index 14.  On GREEN the gate cad-seals its own verdict (the stable seal of
 * capability 1; the single light a stranger runs of capability 12).
 * Main-corpus convention: rc 99 = pass; 1..13 = which Harmony Invariant failed;
 * 14..21 = which terminal-gate assertion failed; 22..24 = the RIPPLE-14 (W4.1) fresh-state
 * self-population falsifier: the public gate over an EMPTY registry must self-populate the
 * thirteen and return a REAL green (count==13 afterwards), never a sealed false-GREEN over
 * nothing (the old code left the count at 0 -> arm 24 fails). */
module corpus_700

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn ct_selftest() -> u64 from "charter_terminal.iii"

fn main() -> u64 { return ct_selftest() }
